11. How To Decide Partition Count

MOST IMPORTANT DESIGN QUESTION.

Formula Approach

Partition count should satisfy:

max(
 producer throughput requirement,
 consumer parallelism requirement
)
Example

Suppose:

Producer throughput:

200 MB/s

One partition handles:

10 MB/s

Needed:

200 / 10 = 20 partitions

Consumer side:

Suppose:

consumer instance handles 5 partitions

Need 4 consumers.

12. Partition Sizing Guidelines

Good practical targets:

Metric	Recommendation
Partition size	10GB–50GB
Messages/sec/partition	Depends on msg size
Total partitions/broker	< 4000 preferred
Replication factor	3
Brokers minimum	3
13. How To Decide Number of Brokers

Depends on:

Storage
Network
CPU
Replication
Throughput
Storage Formula

Example:

Input:

100 MB/s
retention = 7 days
RF=3

Storage:

100 * 60 * 60 * 24 * 7
= 60 TB raw

With RF=3
= 180 TB

If one broker safely stores 10 TB:

180 / 10 = 18 brokers
